---
import ToolLayout from "@/layouts/ToolLayout.astro";
---

<ToolLayout
  title="How Landlord Math Works | Landlord Math Toolkit"
  description="A plain-language overview of the most common rent calculations landlords need."
>
  <section class="hero-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Helper page</p>
    <h1>Four rent calculations that come up constantly.</h1>
    <p class="hero-copy">
      Most day-to-day landlord math fits into a few buckets: partial-month rent, move-in totals, rent changes,
      and late fees. This page gives a quick overview of each one.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="detail-grid">
    <article class="detail-card">
      <h2>Prorated rent and move-ins</h2>
      <p>
        When a tenant moves in or out mid-month, you usually need a partial-month amount. The key variables are
        the monthly rent, the day count, and the proration rule you follow.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="detail-card">
      <h2>Rent changes and late fees</h2>
      <p>
        Rent increases and late fees are simple calculations but trust-sensitive decisions. The math should be
        easy to inspect, while legal and lease compliance should be checked separately.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</ToolLayout>
